overview: The user initiated a request to fix multiple issues in a pull request,
  including security vulnerabilities, functional bugs, and failing Vercel
  deploys. The agent systematically addressed these, starting with lint errors
  and then moving to critical security fixes like replacing a forgeable
  authentication cookie with HMAC-signed sessions. Data validation for API
  endpoints and pagination for CSV exports were also implemented. Significant
  effort was spent debugging Vercel deployment failures, which led to
  refactoring the authentication logic to use Web Crypto API for Edge Runtime
  compatibility, correcting a missing database URL in the Prisma schema, and
  updating Next.js to resolve a critical security vulnerability
  (CVE-2025-66478). This Next.js update introduced further breaking changes,
  requiring adjustments to Prisma configuration and the linting script. Despite
  resolving all code-related issues and ensuring local builds passed, the Vercel
  deploys ultimately failed due to unconfigured environment variables on the
  Vercel platform, which was communicated to the user as the final step.
